Katsina State Chief Judge, Justice Musa Danladi Abubakar has promised to give the state Police command the desired support and cooperation in its efforts to prevent crimes and criminality in the state. Justice Abubakar gave the assurance when he received the newly deployed Commissioner of Police, CP Idris Dauda Dabban on a courtesy visit in his office. He said the police and the judiciary are partners in progress, hence the need for synergy and cooperation from both sides. OAU Student: Retrial Of Adedoyin, 6 Others Begins In Osun Qatar Airways Debut In Kano According to him, the introduction of peace and conflict resolution centres in the state was meant to assist in reducing congestion in police detention facilities and correctional centres. Justice Musa Danladi Abubakar therefore promised to leave his door open to the police for any possible advice, suggestions or needed assistance. The state Commissioner of Police, Idris Dauda Dabban, in his remarks, said the visit is to solicit the CJ’s cooperation and synergize with the command. In a related development, the Katsina State House of Assembly has reaffirmed it’s commitment to assist all security agencies in discharging their duties. The Speaker, Rt. Hon Tasiu Musa Maigari who stated this when he received the new CP during a visit, said as Lawmakers representing the people, they have a vital role to play in ensuring the security of lives and property of the people. POLL He, therefore, assured the support of the lawmakers to the police command in it’s efforts to fight crime and prayed for God’s guidance for the new Commissioner in his assignment. Earlier, the CP Idris Dauda Dabban solicited the support of the lawmakers, called for synergy to address the security menace bedevilling the state. He also appealed for the timely provision of information to the police for quick response whenever the need arises.